    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-18T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-18T05:00:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">315/3–1853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Republic of China</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RANKINJL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-18T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 18, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>973. Re press reports Soviet would accept <persName corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1"
                        >Madame Pandit</persName> or <persName>Benegal Rau</persName> as Secretary
                    General UNO. Foreign Minister informed me Chinese delegate Security Council
                    instructed veto proposal if made formally.</p>
                <p>Foreign Minister hopes necessity for such action will not arise and that US may
                    prevent matter from coming to vote.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RANKINJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rankin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
